producers -> Produces data for kafka cluster in the form of messages into topics
consumer --> consume data from topics
brokers --> nodes of kafka cluster
topic - file which captures stream of messages
paritions - it's for scalability.



// Create a topic
kafka-topics.sh --create --zookeeper nn01.itversity.com:2181,nn02.itversity.com:2181,rm01.itversity.com:2181 --replication-factor 1 --partitions 1 --topic bbastola_kafka
//check topic
kafka-topics.sh --list --zookeeper nn01.itversity.com:2181,nn02.itversity.com:2181,rm01.itversity.com:2181 --topic bbastola_kafka
//create producers
kafka-console-producer.sh --broker-list nn01.itversity.com:6667,nn02.itversity.com:6667,rm01.itversity.com:6667 --topic bbastola_kafka
start typing here and check the cosumer console
//create consumers
kafka-console-consumer.sh --zookeeper nn01.itversity.com:2181,nn02.itversity.com:2181,rm01.itversity.com:2181 --topic bbastola_kafka --from-beginning
message typed in producer should be displayed here